snippet.textDisplay:
Just a lil theory:
It seems like she might pull a hfk by giving us two tracks giving us some explanation as to what will happen in the album because the first track is called "Ashley" and considering stans don't know a lot about Ashley it would only seem fit for that to be an intro/ explanation of what is to come. Since clementine comes before graveyard but Ashley is wearing the white that is at the end of the graveyard video I interpreted that as grown up ashley(not halsey) and since graveyard mv is trying to show that Ashley is just a child I presume the album will show her evolving and the persona that is halsey to form. Also in the clementine mv, it said performed by 'Ashley and Sevain Frangipane'; this could be a mv for halsey but for the persona. I know this sounds confusing but what I'm trying to say it's that it's a mv for this persona so we will learn how this persona developed. Halsey said on twitter that the rectangle box that is on the graveyard cover is suppose to be room 93 so this album will show the persona of halsey to form. Also in the mv Ashley is wearing a heart necklace that has roses. This is important and will come up later in the theory. At the end of the mv Ashley is seen looking sad. The next track after this is called " you should be sad" so I'm going to assume by the context of graveyard that she should be sad about the heartbreak but she isn't. Now I'm going to jump to Without me (it's track #9) In the without me mv there's a rose. Just follow along if you are still reading this. After this, is "Finally/ Beautiful stranger" . In this mv we are shown the two different personas: Ashley and halsey. In this mv Halsey is all dolled up and guess what's on her guitar strap: roses. Roses are going to the main symbol for this album just like butterflies were the main symbol for hfk. Now going onto Suga's interlude. In the cover art for it, it shows a stick person holding an umbrella underneath a rain cloud. what was in clementine? " I'd like to tell you that my sky's not blue, it's violent rain". Also in the cover art, there looks to be a rose. Now for the last track: 929. 929 I think will come full circle back to Ashley since that's her birthday. Thank you if you are still reading this lol I know that was a lengthy theory.



ps: fun lil fact : in the graveyard mv there was an alanis poster and one of the later tracks in the album is alanis's interlude

Show less
